5000|$|A <b>sympiesometer</b> is {{a compact}} and {{lightweight}} type of barometer that was widely used on ships in the 19th century.|$|E
50|$|Alexander James Adie FRSE MWS (1775, Edinburgh - 1859, Edinburgh) was a Scottish {{maker of}} medical instruments, {{optician}} and meteorologist. He was {{the inventor of}} the <b>sympiesometer,</b> patented in 1818.|$|E
