5000|$|Adie {{supplied}} lenses to Joseph Hooker, Charles Darwin and Sir David Brewster and was optician to William IV and to Queen Victoria. He {{invented the}} <b>sympiesometer</b> or marine barometer {{and had a}} small observatory erected long {{before there was a}} public observatory in Edinburgh. [...] He was elected as Fellow of the Royal Society of Edinburgh on 25 January 1819, upon the proposal of Lord F Gray, Sir David Brewster and James Russell.|$|E
